---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="@maplibre-yaml/astro — minimal example">
  <main>
    <h1>@maplibre-yaml/astro — minimal example</h1>
    <p>
      A bare Astro app demonstrating <code>@maplibre-yaml/astro</code>:
      loading features from GeoJSON files, rendering them through
      content collections, and configuring maps with YAML. No styling
      frameworks, no extra integrations — just the API.
    </p>

    <h2>Demos</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <a href="/showcase">Feature-ref showcase</a> — one example per
        GeoJSON geometry type, plus match strategies, display overrides,
        and the most common error paths. Each section shows the
        <code>FeatureRef</code> snippet and the map it produces.
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="/poas/sample">Content collection example</a> — a
        markdown entry with a <code>feature_ref</code> in its
        frontmatter, rendered through
        <code>buildMapConfigFromEntry</code>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How this example is wired</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Global map config:
        <code>src/config/maps.yaml</code> loaded by
        <code>loadGlobalMapConfig</code> in
        <code>src/lib/map-config.ts</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Fixture: <code>src/data/sample.geojson</code> — one feature per
        GeoJSON geometry type (Point, MultiPoint, LineString,
        MultiLineString, Polygon, MultiPolygon, GeometryCollection)
        plus a few edge cases (3D coordinate, no-properties feature,
        single-coord LineString).
      </li>
      <li>
        Content collection: <code>src/content/poas/</code> validated by
        <code>getCollectionItemWithFeatureRefSchema</code>, which
        enforces mutual exclusivity between <code>feature_ref</code> and
        inline geometry fields.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Run locally</h2>
    <pre>cd examples/astro/minimal
pnpm install
pnpm dev</pre>
  </main>
</Layout>
